{
  "stem": "7337.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You had to find countries that would take them, because although we had a carte d'identite, which you had to renew every month-- and you had to slip the officialer a-- a tip every month, otherwise, you didn't get the stamp-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] this was not for permanent residence in France.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "France only offered you [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] temporary residence until you could find a country that would accept you.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the world was basically closed to German Jews.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I mean, there wasn't a European country that would take Jews--",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They'd let you--",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--in on these temporary--",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--temporary permits.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But you had to report every movement to the police.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean, if you traveled somewhere, you had to get a police stamp that you were going on a three-day trip.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it was stamped into your book.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You had a little identity book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] the-- it was very difficult to find countries that would accept you.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "South Africa worked on a-- on a-- on a-- [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] quota system.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "America wouldn't let-- hard-- would let hardly any in.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "There was a small quota, but insignificant.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Australia took some.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Canada took a few.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But the bulk of them had to go to Shanghai, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and that is how the-- one of the reasons why German Jews suddenly arrived in-- in Shanghai, because it was one [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] part of China that took refugees.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Now, it was a well-known fact that the-- the governments knew exactly what was going on in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Their ambassadors have reported back.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, the Pope, at the time, Pius XII, I think it was, was [INAUDIBLE] in Berlin in 1933.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
